@page "/themepatcher"

<PageTitle>ThemePatcher</PageTitle>
<h1 class="text center">ThemePatcher</h1>
<h6 class="center small" style=" justify-content:center; align-content:center; align-self:center; align-items:center;">Get free themes on Oppo or Realme Android device.</h6>
<div class="text small">
    <h5>Tired of buying overpriced themes in Oppo or Realme device? Use This Patcher to get them for free !</h5>
    <p>
        This script lets you unlock all the paid themes, fonts and wallpapers for free from the Theme store in any Oppo or Realme device.
    </p>
</div>
<div class="text">
    <h3 class="small">Disclaimer</h3>
    <p dir="auto" class="small">This Patcher <strong>was not tested and might not work</strong> on any device other than Oppo and Realme.</p>
</div>
<div class="text">
    <h3 class="center hiddenY" style=" margin:0px;">How to use</h3>
    <p>
        This script runs on Windows . While setting up , If you get any prompt in your android device asking you to allow usb debugging , click on the allow button.
        <br/><br/>
        You need to repeat the following actions every time you want to get a paid theme/font/live wallpaper as free.
    </p>
    <ol dir="auto">
        <li class="hidden">
            <p dir="auto">Tap on the build number <strong>seven times</strong> in your android device to enable developer options.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hidden">
            <p dir="auto">Go to developer options , then turn on <strong>usb debugging</strong> and also turn on <strong>Disable Permission Monitoring</strong> <em>if it exists</em>.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hidden">
            <p dir="auto">Connect your phone to the Windows pc using an usb cable.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hidden">
            <p dir="auto">Download and extract the provided Download file <a href="https://github.com/legendsayantan/ThemePatcher/releases">ThemePatcher.zip</a>.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hidden">
            <p dir="auto">Open Theme Store in the android device, choose whatever paid themes you like and click <strong>Free trial</strong>.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hidden">
            <p dir="auto">Run the file <strong>ThemePatcher.bat</strong> in the extracted folder.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hidden">
            <p dir="auto">ThemePatcher should now automatically detect your device and the installed trial theme , font or live wallpaper... will be converted to permanent !</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
    <p class="hidden">
        Once you're done, just close the terminal window and unplug your android device from the pc...
        Turn off dev options if you want to.
    </p>
</div>
<div class="text">
    <h3 class="center hiddenY" style=" margin:0px;">Alternate Method</h3>
    <p dir="auto">If you want to do it through <a href="https://app.webadb.com" rel="nofollow">WebADB</a> , you cannot run the entire batch file.</p>
    <p dir="auto">In that case - go to developer options, enable usb debugging and disable permission monitoring, then connect your android device to <a href="https://app.webadb.com" rel="nofollow">WebADB webpage.</a></p>
    <p dir="auto">Go to Theme store and choose any theme/font/live wallpaper and take a free trial.</p>
    <p> Finally, copy the corresponding code snippet and paste inside the <a href="https://app.webadb.com/shell">Interactive Shell </a> -</p>
    <div class="flex-row center" style="display:flex; flex-direction:row;">
        <h4 class="small" style=" margin:15px; align-content:center; margin-left:75px; margin-right:75px;">Code to Patch Themes</h4>
        <div class="center" style=" margin:0px; padding:0px;">
            <div class="container">
                <a class="btn flex-row" style="margin:0px;" @onclick="@(() => copyText(CodeTheme))">
                    Copy Snippet
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <pre class="notranslate">
        <code>
            @CodeTheme
        </code>
    </pre>
    <div class="flex-row center" style="display:flex; flex-direction:row;">
            <h4 class="small" style=" margin:15px; align-content:center; margin-left:75px; margin-right:75px;">Code to Patch Fonts</h4>
        <div class="center" style=" margin:0px; padding:0px;">
            <div class="container">
                <a class="btn flex-row" style="margin:0px;" @onclick="@(() => copyText(CodeFont))">
                    Copy Snippet
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <pre class="notranslate">
        <code>
@CodeFont
        </code>
    </pre>
    <div class="flex-row center" style="display:flex; flex-direction:row;">
        <h4 class="small" style=" margin:15px; align-content:center; margin-left:75px; margin-right:75px;">Code to Patch Live Wallpapers</h4>
        <div class="center" style=" margin:0px; padding:0px;">
            <div class="container">
                <a class="btn flex-row" style="margin:0px;" @onclick="@(() => copyText(CodeWallpaper))">
                    Copy Snippet
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <pre class="notranslate">
        <code>
@CodeWallpaper
        </code>
    </pre>
</div>
<p>You need to run the entire code of a specific category to correctly patch it. Otherwise, it may not work.</p>
